## Phase 4: CLI — `create-user` Command

New subcommand: `lumiverb create-user`

```
lumiverb create-user --email user@example.com [--role owner|member]
```

Behavior:
1. Prompt for password (hidden input, confirmed twice).
2. Validate: email format, password minimum length (12 characters).
3. Hash password with bcrypt (cost factor 12).
4. Insert into `users` with a generated UUID.
5. Print confirmation: `User created: user@example.com (owner)`.

This is the only way to create users in v1. There is no signup page. Operators add users by running this command on the server.

**Done when:**
```bash
lumiverb create-user --email admin@example.com --role owner
# → prompts for password, confirms, prints success

lumiverb create-user --email admin@example.com --role owner
# → error: email already registered
```

