## Environment Variables

| Var | Required | Description |
|-----|----------|-------------|
| `JWT_SECRET` | Yes | HS256 signing key. Generate: `openssl rand -hex 32` |
| `SMTP_HOST` | For password reset | SMTP server hostname |
| `SMTP_PORT` | For password reset | SMTP port (typically 587) |
| `SMTP_USER` | For password reset | SMTP username |
| `SMTP_PASSWORD` | For password reset | SMTP password |
| `SMTP_FROM` | For password reset | From address for reset emails |
| `APP_HOST` | For password reset | Public URL of the app (for reset links) |

Password reset is optional in v1 — if SMTP vars are absent, the endpoint returns `501 Not Implemented`. Operators who manage users solely via the CLI may not need it.

---

## What Is Not in Scope

- OAuth / SSO (future)
- Multi-tenant self-service signup (future)
- Per-user rate limiting (future)
- Sessions table / refresh tokens — 7-day JWTs are sufficient for v1; add refresh when session length becomes a user issue
- Role-based access control beyond `owner` / `member` distinction — all roles have identical permissions in v1

